entries.femaleVariant: Iris Tanner? S'posed to get you outta here.
entries.maleVariant: Iris Tanner? I'm supposed to get you outta here.

entries.femaleVariant: What difference does it make who you work for?
I don't like it when people take away my right to choose.
You've always got a choice.
Better get moving.
We'd best get a move on.
I'm not going anywhere without my ride. It's sitting in the garage.
Thanks for taking care of my ride.
You were supposed to get my ride out, too.
Why didn't you wanna work with Dakota before?
A – you can get these motors purrin', or B – get lead to the brain.
Think about it.
Took you long enough.
They didn't hurt you?
They didn't hurt you?
That wasn't in the spec. At least tell me it's fast, this ride of yours.
No, it wasn't in the spec. And no, it's not particularly fast, either.
Let's say it's between you and me, huh? I'll make it worth your while.
We'll see how things play out.
No. We were still in the negotiation phase.
They made a pretty solid case, so it was only a matter of time.
Is it worth more than your life?
Probably. But I'm not so much of a mood to explain.
I'll just get some shut-eye, if you don't mind.
Don't mention it.
I'm not crazy about fixers.
Might as well be pimps without the special favors.
Right...
Prefer lining up my own clients, playing by my own rules.
When you're a lone wolf, there's no fixers waiting to steal a cut of your hard-earned cash.
So I take it this is an exception?
And the last, hopefully.
Push came to shove, I'd rather slave under Raffen than be chopped into little pieces.
